## ✅ Features

- User registration and login  
- Complaint submission with form  
- Real-time complaint tracking  
- Chat interface between users and agents  
- Admin dashboard to assign and monitor complaints  
- Role-based access: User, Agent, Admin  
- Secure authentication using JWT  
- RESTful APIs for all major operations  

## 🧠 Technologies Used

- Frontend: React.js, Material UI, Bootstrap, Axios  
- Backend: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Mongoose  
- Authentication: JWT  
- Communication: Chat system via socket.io  

## ⚙ How to Run Locally

1. *Clone the repository:*

git clone https://github.com/Mujasimshaik786/Complaint-registery.git

2. Install dependencies:



# Frontend
cd complaint-registery/frontend
npm install

# Backend
cd ../backend
npm install

3. Run the project:



# Backend
cd backend
npm start

# Frontend (new terminal)
cd ../frontend
npm start

Frontend runs on http://localhost:3000

Backend runs on http://localhost:5000 (if configured)




